    How customer reviews and ratings work

    Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Scarlett Phoenix
    4.0 out of 5 stars *UPDATED* Decided to keep
    Reviewed in the United States on July 13, 2022
    Verified Purchase
    *UPDATED* Decided to keep the laptop after giving it another shot. Still some annoyances, but I'm getting used to them.

    Pros - Pretty fast. Good color on screen. Decent charged battery life. Backlit keyboard (which was a must for me). Full-ish sized keyboard on a small laptop. Thin sized/light weight. Also, when I posted a question on this page, a Chuwi Rep answered very quickly.

    Cons - Keyboard keys feel cheap. Charger port is so close to USB Type C mouse port that I can't charge and use Type C adapter at the same time (this is a pretty big complaint from me). A lot of the "action" keys are sluggish/slow (backspace, delete, arrow keys).

    Jury Still Out - Backlit keyboard doesn't stay "on." (I'm going to check settings to see if there's some kind of time I can change). Power Key should be somewhere else (just my preference). It's easy to click on if you're not used to the set up and are trying to "backspace" which leads to accidentally hitting the power button & making the screen go dark.
